[if Margaux is known]Margaux catches your eye. Her expression is not unkind.[otherwise]Her friend catches your eye. Her expression is not unkind.[end if] It is the expression of a woman who has watched this scene play out many times from many angles and has developed a sympathy for all parties that does not extend to intervention.

'It was nice talking to you,' [if Catherine is known]Catherine[otherwise]the dark-haired woman[end if] says, without turning around, and the sentence falls between you like a curtain made of something very light—silk, or smoke, or the particular substance of which failed evenings are composed.

You are standing in Bemelmans Bar, and the gold ceiling is still golden, and the murals are still full of gentle animals living their gentle lives, and the piano is still playing, and all of it goes on exactly as it was before you arrived, and this is perhaps the most honest thing the room can teach you: that it does not need you, that it was here before you and will be here after, that the rabbits in their top hats will go on promenading through a Central Park that exists on no map and in no season, indifferent to your technique, your method, your three-second rule, your lonely expertise.";
